  "title": "Teaching Position/ Primary/Secondary",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></h2>\n<h3><strong>Selection Criteria</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum <strong>5 years</strong> of teaching experience in elementary and/or secondary schools, or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Experience in tutorial centres for primary and secondary students.</li>\n  <li>Evidence of students successfully passing CEQ/AEIS examinations.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrated good presentation skills and ability to deliver lessons systematically.</li>\n  <li>Proven track record in effective classroom management.</li>\n  <li>Possesses a positive and patient disposition.</li>\n  <li>Proactive in adopting student-centred instruction and delivery.</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills and a strong team player.</li>\n  <li>Able to adapt to different working conditions and demonstrate positive team spirit.</li>\n  <li>Displays a positive attitude towards work and work-related matters.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare and deliver lessons, tutorials, and practical classes according to the course syllabus.</li>\n  <li>Mark and moderate coursework and assessment papers.</li>\n  <li>Prepare examination-related reports.</li>\n  <li>Perform invigilation duties.</li>\n  <li>Provide supervision and consultation to students as required.</li>\n  <li>Provide feedback to the Academic Director (or designate) on class performance.</li>\n  <li>Perform administrative functions related to teaching subjects, as assigned by the Academic Director (or designate).</li>\n  <li>Attend departmental meetings and other meetings organised by the Head, Person-in-Charge (PIC), Academic Director, CEO, or their designate.</li>\n  <li>Carry out any other duties as assigned from time to time by the Academic Director (or designate).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>",
